In a large bowl, combine 3 cups of cracker crumbs and butter; set aside. Divide half of the mushrooms between three greased 13-in. x 9-in. x 2-in. baking dishes. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs; top with remaining mushrooms. Pour cream over all. Sprinkle with buttered crumbs and paprika. Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees F for 30-35 minutes or until golden brown.